    "We stopped at 0.38 since we reached a completely connected graph.",
    "Table 5 summarises the characteristics of the networks generated by using Euclidean Distance at different levels of threshold.",
    "The considerations are similar to the case concerning cosine similarity, with the difference that the number of isolated nodes is lower than the first obtained previously.",
    "It may be associated with considering distance allows for more connections between a larger number of nodes.",
    "Table 6 summarises the characteristics of the networks generated by using Manhattan Distance at different level of threshold."
